  {
    "AlertId": "116089",
    "Headline": "Trains rerouted downtown: Stations along Lake and Wabash closed",
    "ShortDescription": "Orange, Green, Pink and Brown Line trains will be rerouted downtown for work on building a new State/Lake station.",
    "FullDescription": {
      "#cdata-section": "<p><span style=\"color:#F9461C;\"><strong>Orange</strong></span>, <span style=\"color:#009B3A;\"><strong>Green</strong></span>, <strong><span style=\"color:#E27EA6;\">Pink</span> </strong>and <span style=\"color:#62361B;\"><strong>Brown</strong></span><strong> </strong>line trains will be rerouted downtown for work on building a new State/Lake station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#F9461C;\"><strong>Orange</strong></span><strong><span style=\"color:#F9461C;\">&nbsp;</span></strong>and<span style=\"color:#62361B;\"> <strong>Brown </strong></span><strong>Lines<span style=\"color:#62361B;\">:</span> </strong>Trains will operate as one route between Kimball and Midway, via the Wells and Van Buren sides of the Loop, downtown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#009B3A;\"><strong>Green Line</strong></span>: Trains will operate between Harlem/Lake and 63rd street terminals, but via Wells and Van Buren.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#E27EA6;\"><strong>Pink Line</strong><strong>:</strong></span>&nbsp;Trains will operate between 54th/Cermak and Clinton, only. For continuing service, transfer at Clinton to a Green Line train toward 63rd.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Loop &#39;L&#39; and subways: </strong>To transfer between the Loop elevated and the subways, transfer at H.W. Library (Loop elevated lines) and Jackson (Blue or Red lines via subway).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Tip: </strong>Exit at Washington/Wells and board any bus at the Washington/LaSalle Loop Link station for service to Michigan Avenue, Millennium and Grant parks.</em></p>\r\n"
    },
    "SeverityScore": "73",
    "SeverityColor": "06c",
    "SeverityCSS": "planned",
    "Impact": "Planned Work w/Part Closure",
